  "prompt": "How many layers should you wear on cold winter days?",
  "response": "The number of layers you should wear on cold winter days can vary depending on the temperature, your personal tolerance to cold, and the activity you plan to do. However, a general guideline is to wear three layers:\n\n1. **Base Layer:** This is the layer closest to your skin and should be moisture-wicking to keep sweat away and help you stay dry. Materials like merino wool or synthetic fabrics are ideal.\n\n2. **Middle Layer:** This layer provides insulation to retain body heat. Fleece, down, or synthetic insulated jackets are good choices, as they trap warm air close to your body.\n\n3. **Outer Layer:** The outermost layer should be windproof and waterproof to protect you from the elements. A good quality winter coat or jacket serves this purpose.\n\nAdditionally, consider wearing accessories like hats, scarves, gloves, and thermal socks to protect extremities, as well as waterproof boots in wet or snowy conditions. Always adjust the layers based on weather conditions and your level of activity.",
